# VoxyKey

Local tray app for speech-to-text keyboard input with translation.

## Current status
Initial scaffold is implemented:
- Tray app (no GUI window) via `pystray`
- Config file load/save (`toml`)
- Global hotkeys:
  - `hotkey.trigger` for one-shot capture
  - `hotkey.push_to_talk_key` for hold-to-record
- Pipeline wiring for audio -> STT -> translation -> text injection
- Tray language selector (target language) persisted to config
- Translation uses OPUS-MT (`Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-*`) models
- Missing translation model(s) are downloaded at startup into local `models/`

## Run
```bash
uv sync
uv run voxykey
```

## Tray controls
- `Capture now`: one-shot fixed duration recording.
- `Target language`: switch output language (saved to config).
- `Reload config`: reload `config.toml`.

## Default hotkeys
- One-shot: `Ctrl+Shift+Space`
- Push-to-talk: `F8` (hold to record, release to transcribe/translate/type)

## Config path
- Linux: `~/.config/voxykey/config.toml`
- macOS: `~/Library/Application Support/voxykey/config.toml`
- Windows: `%APPDATA%\\voxykey\\config.toml`
